wiki.summary: “Higher We Go” is the opening song of the highly anticipated sequel to their 2017 album Culture. In the song, the trio introduce the notion that despite how high they are (both off of making weed and being at the top of the hip-hop food chain by commanding the game) they will continue to rise up as kings of the genre, and the culture. They are willing to sweat and bleed making beats and spitting bars because they feel obligated to drive the entire hip-hop industry in the right direction. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “Higher We Go” is the opening song of the highly anticipated sequel to their 2017 album Culture. In the song, the trio introduce the notion that despite how high they are (both off of making weed and being at the top of the hip-hop food chain by commanding the game) they will continue to rise up as kings of the genre, and the culture. They are willing to sweat and bleed making beats and spitting bars because they feel obligated to drive the entire hip-hop industry in the right direction. The original instrumental, produced by Metro Boomin, was used in SG Tip’s 2017 single “No Brain.” This track’s instrumental features added production by DJ Durel and Quavo. Read more on Last.fm.
